48
00:03:37,400 --> 00:03:40,400
{\an2}{\pos(208.1,242.25)}第五季  第十一集

49
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:55,020
-党内警告  -不行
- Censure. - No.

50
00:03:55,020 --> 00:03:56,110
我理解马克的意思
I see Mark's point.

51
00:03:56,110 --> 00:03:58,970
根本不可能阻止众议院的共和党人
There is no way to stop the Republicans in the House.

52
00:03:58,970 --> 00:04:00,420
沃克不是可信的证人
Walker's not a reliable witness.

53
00:04:00,430 --> 00:04:02,670
他的证词能被核实吗
Is what he said verifiable?

54
00:04:03,070 --> 00:04:05,120
所以弹劾在所难免
So, impeachment is inevitable.

55
00:04:05,450 --> 00:04:07,430
好吧  那只是假设
Well, that's... that's a presumption.

56
00:04:07,430 --> 00:04:08,770
民主党掌权的参议院
The Democratic Senate

57
00:04:08,770 --> 00:04:12,000
不会愿意弹劾民主党总统
will not be inclined to remove a Democratic president.

58
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:13,440
但他们需要政治掩护
But they need political cover.

59
00:04:13,440 --> 00:04:15,140
党内警告能满足他们
Censure will help them with that.

60
00:04:15,140 --> 00:04:19,210
他们可能提出其他的惩罚
I mean, they might propose other penalties,

61
00:04:19,210 --> 00:04:21,200
罚款  谴责声明
a fine, a statement of condemnation

62
00:04:21,200 --> 00:04:24,280
但他们不会去证实犯罪行为
but they'll stop short of finding criminal wrongdoing.

63
00:04:24,280 --> 00:04:27,160
但如果进展得快  大家都能继续前进了
And if it happens quickly, everyone can move on.

64
00:04:27,160 --> 00:04:29,610
你俩私下商量过这件事吗
Did you two get together on this privately?

65
00:04:29,610 --> 00:04:30,520
没有
No.

66
00:04:31,900 --> 00:04:35,820
弗兰西斯  这是挽救你第一任期的办法
Francis, this is one way to salvage your first term.

67
00:04:35,820 --> 00:04:37,470
沃克本该保持沉默的
Walker was supposed to plead the Fifth.

68
00:04:37,470 --> 00:04:39,080
事情出现了意外变化
Well, things took an unexpected turn.

69
00:04:39,090 --> 00:04:40,700
对  他违背了协议
Yes. He went back on his deal,

70
00:04:40,700 --> 00:04:43,120
因为他和自己的证词一样不可靠
because he's as pliable as his testimony.

71
00:04:43,120 --> 00:04:45,670
马克  我不会被众议院弹劾
Mark, I will not be impeached in the House

72
00:04:45,670 --> 00:04:47,510
那绝对到不了参议院
and it will never get to the Senate.

73
00:04:47,740 --> 00:04:50,120
我们要让加勒特·沃克名誉扫地
We will destroy Garrett Walker's credibility

74
00:04:50,120 --> 00:04:53,220
这事便会不攻自破
and the case will fall apart.

75
00:04:53,320 --> 00:04:54,180
好吧
Okay.

76
00:05:05,400 --> 00:05:07,300
我能得到豁免权吗
Can I get immunity?

77
00:05:07,570 --> 00:05:09,210
看你能提供什么信息
Depends on what you give them.

78
00:05:09,210 --> 00:05:10,660
我会联系副主席
I'll reach out to a ranking member,

79
00:05:10,660 --> 00:05:12,230
但你无法匿名
but you're not gonna get anonymity...

80
00:05:12,230 --> 00:05:13,120
凯茜
Cathy.

81
00:05:14,470 --> 00:05:16,430
-简  -你好
- Jane. - Hello?

82
00:05:17,180 --> 00:05:20,100
我为你牵肠挂肚  你能相信发生这种事吗
You've been on my mind. Can you believe what's going on?

83
00:05:20,110 --> 00:05:21,530
抱歉失陪一下
Excuse me for a moment.

84
00:05:22,510 --> 00:05:25,580
就像我母亲说的  "简直是一团乱麻"
As my mother used to say, "It's a red hot mess."

85
00:05:25,580 --> 00:05:28,240
弗兰克·安德伍德倒霉不代表你也得遭殃
Frank Underwood's demise doesn't have to be yours.

86
00:05:28,240 --> 00:05:29,190
还有许多非营利性
There are non-profits,

87
00:05:29,190 --> 00:05:31,910
民间组织非常希望和你合作
NGOs that would be dying to work with you.

88
00:05:31,910 --> 00:05:34,100
据我所知  我的工作还没丢
Well, as far as I know, I still have a job.

89
00:05:34,100 --> 00:05:35,700
当然没有
No, of course.

90
00:05:35,760 --> 00:05:38,040
但谁知道他们接下来会去查谁
But who knows who they'll come after next?

91
00:05:38,040 --> 00:05:40,340
我本来就不是核心圈子的人
I was never part of their inner circle.

92
00:05:40,380 --> 00:05:42,980
你找莫琳很聪明  她是个好律师
You were smart to go with Maureen. She's a good lawyer.

93
00:05:42,980 --> 00:05:45,690
要说谁能帮你全身而退  就是她了
If someone can find you an exit, it's her.

94
00:05:45,690 --> 00:05:47,760
我不会就这么轻易退场的
Well, I'm not gonna go away easily,

95
00:05:47,760 --> 00:05:50,090
所以多谢你的关心  简
so thank you for your concern, Jane.

96
00:05:50,090 --> 00:05:51,590
我是关心
It is concern.

97
00:05:53,140 --> 00:05:54,870
你认为副总统
do you think the vice president

98
00:05:54,870 --> 00:05:57,640
知道这些事情吗
had any knowledge of this stuff?

99
00:05:58,490 --> 00:06:01,510
我说了  我真的不知道
Well, as I said, I have no idea.

100
00:06:03,720 --> 00:06:07,700
如果克莱尔挺过这关  成了总统
If... if Claire survives this and becomes president,

101
00:06:07,700 --> 00:06:09,500
那你要怎么办
where does that leave you?

102
00:06:11,340 --> 00:06:14,160
我好歹也打拼了三十多年  简
Well, I've been at this for 30 years, Jane,

103
00:06:14,160 --> 00:06:15,920
我想我还是能挺过去的
so I think I can survive.

104
00:06:15,920 --> 00:06:19,100
亲爱的  我不是想吓唬你
Oh, honey, I didn't mean to alarm you.

105
00:06:19,440 --> 00:06:21,150
我也没害怕
I'm not alarmed.

106
00:06:21,470 --> 00:06:23,010
我只是想说
All I'm trying to say,

107
00:06:23,110 --> 00:06:24,580
我支持你
I'm on your side.

108
00:06:32,180 --> 00:06:35,200
如果是在继续当总统还是下台之间选择的话
If it's the difference in being in office or being out,

109
00:06:35,200 --> 00:06:36,710
我们可以想办法绕过去
we can work around that.

110
00:06:36,710 --> 00:06:38,530
戴着手铐想办法吧
Working in handcuffs.

111
00:06:38,530 --> 00:06:40,810
党内警告是个挫折  但还没有输
Censure is a setback. It's not a loss.

112
00:06:40,810 --> 00:06:43,360
你还真是自信满满  执拗得很啊
You're very confident and very insistent.

113
00:06:44,120 --> 00:06:45,580
我们会撑过去的  弗兰西斯
We can come out of this, Francis.

114
00:06:45,580 --> 00:06:46,610
你是说你自己吧
No, you mean you can.

115
00:06:46,630 --> 00:06:47,900
哪怕就一次  你能不能
Can you, for once,

116
00:06:47,900 --> 00:06:51,310
干脆点  接受开价  别再还价了
just take something at face value instead of fighting it?

117
00:06:51,420 --> 00:06:54,510
就好像我过去造的孽能洗清似的
As if I can be washed clean of past sins.

118
00:06:54,820 --> 00:06:56,820
-你认识我多久了  -很久了
- How long have you known me? - Forever.

119
00:06:56,820 --> 00:06:58,350
那你有多了解我
How well do you know me?

120
00:06:58,350 --> 00:07:00,040
就算你克莱尔·安德伍德
How, in your wildest imagination,

121
00:07:00,040 --> 00:07:01,520
再怎么尽情发动想象力
could you, Claire Underwood,

122
00:07:01,520 --> 00:07:03,760
也不该以为我会接受这个
think I would be okay with this?

123
00:07:05,540 --> 00:07:06,990
求你考虑一下吧
Think about it, please.

124
00:07:06,990 --> 00:07:09,840
这关乎我的总统之位
This is the fate of my presidency!

125
00:07:10,440 --> 00:07:13,630
人民想原谅你
The people want to forgive you.

126
00:07:13,960 --> 00:07:15,000
接受吧
Let them.

127
00:07:22,050 --> 00:07:24,040
快点出来  再给我讲讲
Come out here already. Give me the rest of it.

128
00:07:24,650 --> 00:07:27,450
汉默施密特是个彻头彻尾的工作狂
Hammerschmidt is a straight-up workaholic.

129
00:07:27,810 --> 00:07:29,920
但是他就快查出什么了
But... he's getting close.

130
00:07:30,380 --> 00:07:31,570
线索慢慢拼凑起来了
Putting the pieces together.

131
00:07:31,570 --> 00:07:32,980
他还查得这么起劲做什么
What's he still grinding so hard for?

132
00:07:32,980 --> 00:07:35,270
看来沃克就要扳倒安德伍德了
Looks like Walker's gonna bring Underwood down.

133
00:07:41,280 --> 00:07:42,960
我不想再谈工作了
I don't wanna do this anymore.

134
00:07:44,720 --> 00:07:46,830
佐伊·巴恩斯  瑞秋·波斯纳
Zoe Barnes. Rachel Posner.

135
00:07:46,830 --> 00:07:48,240
肖恩  别说了
Sean, please, I...

136
00:07:48,270 --> 00:07:49,700
是我想把他的调查拉回来
I was the one trying to get him back on that.

137
00:07:49,700 --> 00:07:52,910
-结果害得我被解雇了  -能不说这些了吗
- That's what got me fired. - Can we stop talking about this?

138
00:07:53,340 --> 00:07:54,260
-我的酒呢  -别这样
- Where's my drink? - Don't do that.

139
00:07:54,260 --> 00:07:56,100
看着我  看我
Look at me. Look.

140
00:07:57,990 --> 00:08:00,710
我这就  不说了
This is me... not talking.

141
00:08:03,120 --> 00:08:05,140
过来  过来
Come here. Come here.

142
00:08:07,430 --> 00:08:10,240
如果有我能帮忙的地方  就告诉我
But if I can be of any help, you let me know.

143
00:08:14,530 --> 00:08:15,240
看我不收拾你
You're gonna get it.

144
00:08:15,240 --> 00:08:16,370
让我也喝一口
Give me a taste of that.

145
00:08:23,330 --> 00:08:24,210
慢点
Slow down.

146
00:08:27,730 --> 00:08:28,680
靠边停
Pull over!

147
00:08:33,730 --> 00:08:36,000
你今天骑得很使劲啊  总统先生  还好吗
You're going pretty hard, Mr. President. You okay?

148
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:38,820
对于一个命运悬而未决的人来说  够好的了
Well enough for a man whose fate is hanging in the balance.

149
00:08:38,820 --> 00:08:39,650
不对
No.

150
00:08:40,350 --> 00:08:41,600
你的命运已经定了
Your fate is sealed.

151
00:08:41,600 --> 00:08:42,740
怎么说
Oh, how's that?

152
00:08:42,740 --> 00:08:44,380
你又"预见"到了什么了吗  艾瑞克
You have a vision for me, Eric?

153
00:08:44,380 --> 00:08:46,410
就算你被弹劾定罪
Even if you're impeached and convicted...

154
00:08:46,610 --> 00:08:47,970
你还是会创造历史
you still make history.

155
00:08:48,480 --> 00:08:50,140
奥古斯都·安德伍德只是又一个
Augustus Underwood was just another redneck

156
00:08:50,140 --> 00:08:51,980
选错了立场的农民罢了
who died fighting for the wrong side,

157
00:08:51,980 --> 00:08:54,100
除了你和我没人记得住他
forgotten by everyone but you and me.

158
00:08:54,670 --> 00:08:57,400
但如果弗兰西斯·安德伍德下台了呢
But if Francis Underwood is removed from office?

159
00:08:57,590 --> 00:08:59,070
你的遗产也不会消散
Your legacy won't die.

160
00:08:59,740 --> 00:09:01,230
反而会更加牢固
It'll be solidified.

161
00:09:01,990 --> 00:09:03,340
你会遗臭万年
You'll be infamous.

162
00:09:03,620 --> 00:09:06,300
政治遗产和遗臭万年可不是一回事
Legacy and infamy are not the same thing.

163
00:09:06,300 --> 00:09:07,780
你将被人铭记  谁在乎原因呢
You'll be remembered. Who cares why?

164
00:09:07,780 --> 00:09:09,260
我得回去了
I have to get back.

165
00:09:09,890 --> 00:09:11,420
等等  听我解释一下
Hold up. Let me explain.

166
00:09:12,450 --> 00:09:13,490
弗兰西斯
Francis.

167
00:09:36,140 --> 00:09:37,100
弗兰西斯
Francis.

168
00:09:40,110 --> 00:09:41,060
弗兰西斯
Francis?

169
00:09:56,070 --> 00:09:57,220
我说清楚
Just to be clear,

170
00:09:57,420 --> 00:10:00,040
我其实一直都知道你在看着我
it's not that I haven't always known you were there.

171
00:10:00,390 --> 00:10:02,890
只是我对你的情感很复杂
It's that I have mixed feelings about you.

172
00:10:03,530 --> 00:10:05,990
我质疑你的意图
I question your intentions...

173
00:10:06,160 --> 00:10:09,600
而且我对关注感到矛盾
and I'm ambivalent about attention.

174
00:10:09,960 --> 00:10:11,720
但别当我是针对你
But don't take it personally.

175
00:10:11,750 --> 00:10:14,220
我对每个人的感觉几乎都是这样的
It's how I feel about most everybody.

176
00:10:14,580 --> 00:10:16,640
我们怎能相信他说的话呢
How can we trust anything he says?

