546
00:35:13,350 --> 00:35:15,920
要是麦卡伦给了你什么  我们应该上交
If Macallan gave you something, we should hand it over.

547
00:35:20,760 --> 00:35:21,920
你喜欢吗
Did you like it?

548
00:35:24,240 --> 00:35:25,130
什么
What?

549
00:35:27,300 --> 00:35:28,650
监视我
Watching me.

550
00:35:35,810 --> 00:35:36,850
喜欢
Yes.

551
00:35:42,000 --> 00:35:43,720
你喜欢你看见的吗
You liked what you saw?

552
00:35:47,790 --> 00:35:49,160
这是你来找我的原因吗
That why you came here?

553
00:36:02,530 --> 00:36:03,640
那好吧
Well, then.

554
00:36:43,930 --> 00:36:46,940
我要去健身房  跑步消解压力
Going to the gym. Run off some of this stress.

555
00:36:48,640 --> 00:36:49,870
你的教练呢
Where's your trainer?

556
00:36:50,090 --> 00:36:53,700
他有一段时间都不会来了
Oh, he won't be coming around for a while.

557
00:36:56,440 --> 00:36:59,370
他有个表情我可不会怀念
He did have a facial expression I won't miss.

558
00:37:00,610 --> 00:37:02,000
是吗
Is that so?

559
00:37:02,210 --> 00:37:05,280
那种凝固的笑  很瘆人
Sort of perma-smile. It was creepy.

560
00:37:06,230 --> 00:37:08,020
也许他只是开心罢了
Maybe he's just happy.

561
00:37:10,300 --> 00:37:12,330
我不担心开心
Happiness isn't my concern.

562
00:37:12,950 --> 00:37:14,540
现在不  从来都不
Not now, not ever.

563
00:37:21,790 --> 00:37:24,050
这局面太不幸了  克莱尔
It's a tragic situation, Claire.

564
00:37:24,050 --> 00:37:26,540
-我知道  -我可以给你看看正在发生的事
- I know. - I could show you what's happening.

565
00:37:26,540 --> 00:37:28,020
我看过照片了
I've seen the images.

566
00:37:28,020 --> 00:37:31,770
务必要让民众知道霍姆斯城正在发生什么
It's important people know what's going on in Homs.

567
00:37:32,180 --> 00:37:33,570
你改主意了吗
Are you having second thoughts?

568
00:37:33,570 --> 00:37:35,930
只是现在时机还不到
It's just the timing isn't right yet.

569
00:37:35,930 --> 00:37:38,360
因为你丈夫得不到支持
Because your husband doesn't have the support.

570
00:37:38,720 --> 00:37:39,730
我们得有理有据
We need to make a case.

571
00:37:39,730 --> 00:37:41,990
你做声明之前  让全世界做好准备
Prepare the world for when you make a statement.

572
00:37:41,990 --> 00:37:45,650
我认为弗兰西斯得来做主导
I think Francis needs to be front and center on this.

573
00:37:47,470 --> 00:37:50,080
你没查到麦卡伦告诉佩特罗夫什么了
You never found out what Macallan told Petrov?

574
00:37:50,880 --> 00:37:54,040
我的线人说  他没说什么真正有用的
My sources say he never gave him anything concrete.

575
00:37:54,050 --> 00:37:57,140
-他给了莉安一些东西  -我们希望如此
- Well, he gave LeAnn something. - Well, that was our hope.

576
00:37:58,110 --> 00:38:00,270
也许是时候再把她请回来了
Maybe it's time to invite her back in.

577
00:38:01,430 --> 00:38:03,820
也许吧  我得上楼了
Maybe. I need to get back upstairs.

578
00:38:03,970 --> 00:38:07,280
下次在我办公室见
The next time we meet will be in my office.

579
00:38:08,300 --> 00:38:11,190
我不觉得你丈夫该做主导
I... I don't think your husband should be front and center.

580
00:38:14,010 --> 00:38:15,580
应该是你
I think it should be you.

581
00:38:17,060 --> 00:38:18,450
我没问你的意见
I didn't ask you what you think.

582
00:38:18,450 --> 00:38:20,220
你得有所准备  克莱尔
You need to be armed, Claire.

583
00:38:21,120 --> 00:38:22,640
无论他怎样
It's important that you can walk away

584
00:38:22,640 --> 00:38:24,890
你务必得能全身而退
from anything that happens to him.

585
00:38:35,730 --> 00:38:37,170
去他们的
They can kiss my ass.

586
00:38:37,170 --> 00:38:39,660
参议员韦斯特维尔特有意要我
I got an offer from Senator Westervelt.

587
00:38:39,660 --> 00:38:40,440
我也在找
I'm looking, too.

588
00:38:40,450 --> 00:38:43,070
但想下这艘船越来越困难了
But it's getting harder and harder to get off this ship.

589
00:38:56,800 --> 00:38:58,640
我妻子在哪
Where is my wife?

590
00:38:59,670 --> 00:39:01,210
她去哪了
Where has she gone?

591
00:39:02,380 --> 00:39:05,540
如果她是你妻子  你不会想知道吗
If she was your wife, wouldn't you wonder?

592
00:39:26,430 --> 00:39:27,990
好  安德伍德夫人
Yes, Mrs. Underwood.

593
00:39:55,110 --> 00:39:57,960
别担心  这事没发生过
Don't worry. This never happened.

594
00:39:59,210 --> 00:40:00,650
不用你告诉我
You don't have to tell me.

595
00:40:04,960 --> 00:40:07,430
-道格  -该死
- Doug. - Shit.

596
00:40:08,430 --> 00:40:09,510
我该过去吗
Should I come in?

597
00:40:11,560 --> 00:40:14,680
不  除非你把你手里的东西给我
No. Not until you give me what you've got.

598
00:40:19,690 --> 00:40:21,130
总统先生
Mr. President.

599
00:40:21,130 --> 00:40:25,930
"一位白宫内部人士透露
"A source deep within the White House...

600
00:40:26,860 --> 00:40:29,380
安德伍德总统确实
confirms President Underwood

601
00:40:29,390 --> 00:40:32,110
曾利用可疑情报
used questionable intelligence

602
00:40:32,110 --> 00:40:34,780
为关闭投票中心找理由
to justify voting center closures,

603
00:40:34,780 --> 00:40:37,940
从而使选举陷入了混乱"
which threw the election into chaos."

604
00:40:40,220 --> 00:40:41,770
你觉得会是谁
Who do you think it is?

605
00:40:44,190 --> 00:40:45,740
可能是格林
Green, probably.

606
00:40:45,740 --> 00:40:48,470
-我们高估了他的忠诚  -我明白了
- We overestimated his loyalty. - I see.

607
00:40:50,730 --> 00:40:51,690
要不
I mean...

608
00:40:53,250 --> 00:40:54,770
还能是谁
who else could it be?

609
00:40:57,030 --> 00:40:58,220
我能做些什么
How can I help?

610
00:40:59,240 --> 00:41:01,950
我们得自救
We need to save ourselves here.

611
00:41:01,950 --> 00:41:05,620
-这事对我俩都很不利  凯茜  -我明白
- It's as much your head as mine, Cathy. - I understand.

612
00:41:23,650 --> 00:41:25,660
我需要你编写额外的材料
I need you to create additional documents

613
00:41:25,660 --> 00:41:27,620
为追捕卡拉比找理由
that justify going after Kalabi.

614
00:41:27,630 --> 00:41:31,190
制造书面痕迹来支撑我们
A paper trail that will support our actions

615
00:41:31,190 --> 00:41:33,960
选举日在田纳西采取的行动
that we took on Election Day in Tennessee.

616
00:41:34,190 --> 00:41:35,900
我不确定
I'm not sure...

617
00:41:36,850 --> 00:41:38,930
该是什么样的材料
what those documents would be.

618
00:41:38,930 --> 00:41:40,630
可你够聪明  对吧  凯茜
Well, but you're smart, Cathy, aren't you?

619
00:41:40,630 --> 00:41:41,790
你会想到的
I mean, you can figure it out.

620
00:41:41,800 --> 00:41:44,430
让我看看你有多聪明吧
Why don't you just show me how smart you are.

621
00:41:46,620 --> 00:41:50,180
-当然  总统先生  -还有在联合国的演讲
- Of course, Mr. President. - And the presentation at the UN.

622
00:41:51,230 --> 00:41:53,520
-关于叙利亚的  -必须进行
- With Syria? - It needs to happen.

623
00:41:54,250 --> 00:41:56,690
-好吧  -可能会引起非议
- Very well. - There's a possibility of talks,

624
00:41:56,690 --> 00:42:00,950
但我们得让所有相关方重新回到谈判桌上
but we need to get all the interested parties back to the table.

625
00:42:00,960 --> 00:42:02,090
当然
Of course.

626
00:42:05,370 --> 00:42:07,630
你是个好外交官  凯茜
You're a good diplomat, Cathy.

627
00:42:08,430 --> 00:42:10,150
谢谢  总统先生
Thank you, Mr. President.

628
00:42:10,520 --> 00:42:12,520
另外  克莱尔呢
And where is Claire?

629
00:42:12,520 --> 00:42:14,740
她现在需要保持些距离
She needed a little distance right now.

630
00:42:14,740 --> 00:42:17,530
直到我们看清我到底怎么回事
Till we find out what's happening with me.

631
00:42:18,610 --> 00:42:22,200
所以我现在必须指望你了  凯茜
That's why I need to rely on you, Cathy. Now.

632
00:42:26,020 --> 00:42:28,620
很高兴你这么想  弗兰西斯
Well, I'm glad you feel that way, Francis.

633
00:42:55,550 --> 00:42:58,130
是我  我可以见面了
Yes. I'm ready to meet.

634
00:42:58,620 --> 00:43:01,120
我现在就要见面  马上
I wanna meet now. Right now.

635
00:43:21,170 --> 00:43:22,760
在一次
After a tumultuous election,

636
00:43:22,760 --> 00:43:24,450
前所未有的混乱选举后
the likes of which have never been seen,

637
00:43:24,450 --> 00:43:26,340
美国面临着更多的问题
America faces more questions...

638
00:43:26,340 --> 00:43:28,890
我现在一堆破事  没时间应付你
Shit is insane right now. I don't have any more time for you.

639
00:43:28,890 --> 00:43:30,920
如果最近从白宫泄露出来的情报
If the recent leaks coming out of the White House

640
00:43:30,930 --> 00:43:33,100
得到证实  总统将面临...
prove to be true, the president could face...

641
00:43:33,100 --> 00:43:34,810
白宫身份牌  你从哪弄的
A White House ID? Where did you get that?

642
00:43:34,810 --> 00:43:36,250
我还以为是你给的
I thought this came from you.

643
00:43:36,840 --> 00:43:38,420
你说什么呢
What the hell are you talking about?

644
00:43:38,810 --> 00:43:41,560
-我现在是副新闻发言人了  -去你妈的
- I'm deputy press secretary. - The fuck you are.

645
00:43:41,560 --> 00:43:43,080
我接到了副总统办公室的电话
I got a call from the vice president's office,

646
00:43:43,080 --> 00:43:44,350
让我过来
asking me to come in.

647
00:43:44,350 --> 00:43:45,810
我到的时候  这个已经准备好了
And when I got here, this was waiting for me.

648
00:43:45,820 --> 00:43:47,810
我刚才一小时都在办手续
I just spent the last hour doing my paperwork.

649
00:43:49,510 --> 00:43:50,930
我没时间跟你胡扯
I don't have time for this.

650
00:43:50,930 --> 00:43:53,110
加勒特·沃克总统的爆炸性证词
President Garrett Walker's bombshell testimony, which...

651
00:43:53,110 --> 00:43:55,470
我有国务卿杜兰特的辞职信
I have Secretary Durant's resignation.

652
00:43:55,470 --> 00:43:57,270
我相信她就是泄密者
I believe she was the leak,

653
00:43:57,280 --> 00:43:58,830
并且可能要为
and might have to take responsibility

654
00:43:58,830 --> 00:44:00,760
选举当晚发生的事负责
for whatever happened on election night.

655
00:44:00,760 --> 00:44:02,660
先生  司法委员会现在随时
Sir, the judiciary could issue a resolution

656
00:44:02,660 --> 00:44:04,420
会发出弹劾决议了
for impeachment any day now.

657
00:44:04,420 --> 00:44:07,320
我们得现实地面对这事对总统的伤害
We need to be realistic about damage to the president

658
00:44:07,320 --> 00:44:08,800
即便参议院不定罪
even if the Senate doesn't convict.

659
00:44:08,800 --> 00:44:10,220
你承诺的是党内警告
You promised us censure.

660
00:44:10,220 --> 00:44:12,130
杜兰特的泄密已经起到同样的效果了  不是吗
Well, Durant's leak took care of that, didn't it?

661
00:44:12,700 --> 00:44:14,370
我们有个应对参议院的计划
So, we have a plan for the Senate.

662
00:44:14,370 --> 00:44:16,840
我建议重点保护副总统
I suggest we work on protecting the vice president.

663
00:44:17,730 --> 00:44:21,740
确保她在整个过程中能全身而退
Make sure she exits this whole process unscathed.

664
00:44:21,740 --> 00:44:23,260
我们要怎么才能做到
And how do we do that?

665
00:44:24,360 --> 00:44:28,480
声称不知情  副总统没审阅任何相关信息
Plead ignorance. The vice president wasn't read into anything.

666
00:44:28,810 --> 00:44:29,940
什么也不知道
Didn't know anything.

667
00:44:29,940 --> 00:44:32,250
-也什么都没做  -不行的
- Didn't do anything. - That won't play.

668
00:44:32,610 --> 00:44:34,860
她会看上去不知情  但人们知道并非如此
She'll look uninformed, and the people know she isn't.

669
00:44:34,860 --> 00:44:37,170
距离会让她看起来无辜
Oh, the distance will help her look innocent.

670
00:44:37,170 --> 00:44:41,320
无辜或有罪  有能力或没用  不管怎样
Innocent, guilty, capable, incompetent, whatever it is...

671
00:44:41,320 --> 00:44:44,300
公众都会往反方向想
the public is going to think the opposite.

672
00:44:44,600 --> 00:44:46,400
所以真是怎么都输
So, really there is no winning.

673
00:44:47,700 --> 00:44:49,320
照你的意思来吧
Whatever you think is best.

674
00:44:49,320 --> 00:44:51,780
如果我被判无罪  你会有四年时间
You're gonna have four years to prove yourself

675
00:44:51,780 --> 00:44:55,030
在位子上证明自己  希望是八年
on the inside if I'm acquitted. Hopefully, eight.

676
00:44:55,030 --> 00:44:56,930
但如果我被判有罪呢
But what happens if I'm not acquitted?

677
00:44:56,930 --> 00:44:57,990
我们现在不用考虑那个
We don't have to deal with that right now.

678
00:44:57,990 --> 00:44:59,100
不  我想听到一个计划
No, I want to hear a plan.

679
00:44:59,100 --> 00:44:59,880
这正是找你来的原因
That's why you're here.

680
00:44:59,880 --> 00:45:01,350
给我冷冰冰  硬梆梆的事实
To give me the cold, hard facts.

681
00:45:01,350 --> 00:45:04,150
我的盘算不比您高明  总统先生
Oh, your calculus is as good as mine, Mr. President.

682
00:45:04,150 --> 00:45:06,200
根本没有计划
There is no plan.

683
00:45:06,590 --> 00:45:10,330
只能拖住司法委员会  稳住参议院
Except slow down judiciary, secure the Senate.

684
00:45:22,490 --> 00:45:24,390
我担心一个人
I'm concerned about someone.

685
00:45:25,030 --> 00:45:26,110
劳拉·莫雷蒂
Laura Moretti.

686
00:45:27,240 --> 00:45:28,180
为什么把这个也放进来
Why did you include this?

687
00:45:28,180 --> 00:45:31,930
你跟克莱尔谈这个什么劳拉·莫雷蒂
You and Claire talking about a Laura Moretti?

688
00:45:32,290 --> 00:45:35,470
我想让你知道  先生  她知道了
I wanted you to know, sir, that she knows.

689
00:45:37,270 --> 00:45:38,760
我在名单上帮你插了队
I jumped you on the list.

690
00:45:39,250 --> 00:45:40,990
好获得肝脏捐赠
To receive a donor liver.

691
00:45:41,240 --> 00:45:43,930
我强迫卫生和人类服务部部长调高了你的排名
I forced the HHS Secretary to move you up.

692
00:45:43,930 --> 00:45:46,770
-那不可能  -我威胁了她  先生
- That's not possible. - I threatened her, sir.

693
00:45:47,310 --> 00:45:51,470
这是前所未有的道德违规  但我不后悔这样做
It was an unprecedented ethical violation. But I don't regret it.

694
00:45:54,090 --> 00:45:56,850
我独守这个秘密  好让你...
I kept it to myself, so that you would...

695
00:45:57,160 --> 00:45:59,630
在有人发现时可以合理推诿
have plausible deniability if anyone found out.

696
00:46:00,610 --> 00:46:02,610
我也没告诉安德伍德夫人
I didn't tell Mrs. Underwood either.

697
00:46:03,580 --> 00:46:04,870
她是从别处知道的
She learned another way.

698
00:46:05,790 --> 00:46:08,230
她知道却没告诉我
She knew and didn't tell me.

699
00:46:09,060 --> 00:46:10,060
看起来是这样
Seems so.

700
00:46:12,330 --> 00:46:14,270
她对耶茨的监控反应如何
And how did she react to the Yates surveillance?

701
00:46:14,270 --> 00:46:15,750
那个她怎么说的
What did she say about that?

702
00:46:16,460 --> 00:46:18,510
她没对我表达她的感受  先生
She didn't show her feelings to me, sir.

703
00:46:27,670 --> 00:46:29,180
你救了我的命
You saved my life.

704
00:46:31,830 --> 00:46:33,110
我与你同在  先生
I'm here for you, sir.

705
00:46:33,880 --> 00:46:34,850
直到永远
Always.

706
00:46:40,120 --> 00:46:42,280
你对安德伍德夫人有疑虑吗
Do you have concerns about Mrs. Underwood?

707
00:46:42,480 --> 00:46:45,120
-你有吗  -我永远不会这样讲
- Do you? - I would never say that.

708
00:46:47,230 --> 00:46:48,610
我要给你看点东西
I want to show you something.

709
00:46:52,540 --> 00:46:55,760
有45分钟我不清楚她的行踪
There's 45 minutes where I can't account for her whereabouts.

710
00:46:55,760 --> 00:46:58,320
我不知道她去了哪里  见了什么人
I don't know where she went or who she saw.

711
00:46:59,570 --> 00:47:01,040
但是她对我说谎了
But she lied to me.

712
00:47:12,580 --> 00:47:15,830
我认为你应该休息一下  先生
I, uh... I think you should get some rest, sir.

713
00:47:33,120 --> 00:47:35,480
总统没有让我审阅
The president didn't read me in.

714
00:47:36,420 --> 00:47:38,520
我不在房间里
I wasn't in the room.

715
00:47:39,710 --> 00:47:41,500
总统没有让我审阅
The president didn't read me in.

716
00:47:41,500 --> 00:47:42,870
我不在房间里
I wasn't in the room.

717
00:47:43,460 --> 00:47:46,060
我对此毫不知情
I didn't know anything about it.

718
00:47:46,760 --> 00:47:49,590
总统没有让我审阅
The president didn't read me in.

719
00:47:50,830 --> 00:47:52,740
我不在房间里
I wasn't in the room.

720
00:47:52,740 --> 00:47:54,710
我对此毫不知情
I didn't know anything about it.

721
00:47:58,020 --> 00:47:59,790
怎么样  弗兰西斯
How's that, Francis?

722
00:48:10,700 --> 00:48:14,580
最新消息  国务卿凯瑟琳·杜兰特
This is just in. Secretary of State Catherine Durant

723
00:48:14,580 --> 00:48:17,510
将在众议院司法委员会作证
to appear in front of the House Judiciary Committee.

724
